BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 604.50 Tm (Good morning everyone, and welcome. Today's session has a slightly long name - Collections,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 589.30 Tm (Class Relationships, and File Input-Output - so let me tell you the one simple idea that ties all) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 574.10 Tm (three together. Everything we do today is about one thing: managing data.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 553.90 Tm (Think about it. A program is really just data plus things we do to that data. So we need good ways) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 538.70 Tm (to hold it, organise it, and save it. And that is exactly our three topics. Collections are about holding) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 523.50 Tm (lots of data in memory while the program runs. Class relationships are about how our objects) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 508.30 Tm (connect to each other in a tidy way. And File Input-Output is about saving data onto the disk so it) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 493.10 Tm (survives after the program closes.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 472.90 Tm (So even though it looks like three separate topics, keep that thread in your mind - it is all data) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 457.70 Tm (management. By the end of today, you will have the full toolkit for handling data in any Java) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 442.50 Tm (program, and especially in the Spring projects you will build later.) Tj ET
