0.040 0.520 1.000 rg 58.00 729.00 496.00 1.40 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.420 0.420 0.460 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 713.00 Tm (ON SCREEN) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 697.00 Tm (Three cards: store 500 names; remove the item at index 200; check if 'Ravi' is already present.) Tj ET
0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 683.50 3.00 35.50 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 672.50 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 656.50 Tm (Before we learn collections, let me convince you why we even need them. You already know) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 641.30 Tm (arrays, right? An array is a fixed row of boxes. Arrays are fine, until they are not - and the three) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 626.10 Tm (cards on screen show exactly where they fall apart.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 605.90 Tm (First card: you make an array for 500 student names. Great. But then a 501st student joins. Now) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 590.70 Tm (what? An array cannot grow - you decided its size at the start and you are stuck. You would have) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 575.50 Tm (to make a whole new bigger array and copy everything over by hand. Annoying.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 555.30 Tm (Second card: you want to remove the student at position 200. With an array, removing one from) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 540.10 Tm (the middle means you have to manually shift every single student after it one step to the left, to fill) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 524.90 Tm (the gap. Imagine doing that for thousands of records. With a collection? One line - list dot remove.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 509.70 Tm (Done.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 489.50 Tm (Third card: you want to check, 'is Ravi already in my list?' With an array, you write a loop and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 474.30 Tm (check each one. With a collection, again, one method - contains - and it tells you.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 454.10 Tm (So here is the bottom line. Arrays are fixed in size and have no built-in helpers. Collections, on the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 438.90 Tm (other hand, can grow and shrink freely, and they come loaded with handy methods. That is why) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 423.70 Tm (they exist - to take all that painful manual work off your plate.) Tj ET
0.040 0.520 1.000 rg 58.00 408.50 3.00 270.00 re f
