0.040 0.520 1.000 rg 58.00 372.50 496.00 1.40 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.420 0.420 0.460 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 356.50 Tm (ON SCREEN) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 340.50 Tm (A colour-coded tree: Iterable at the top, then Collection branching into List, Set, and Queue. Map is shown) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 327.00 Tm (separately in its own box.) Tj ET
0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 313.50 3.00 49.00 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 302.50 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 286.50 Tm (This slide is the family tree of collections, and I want you to keep this mental map, because) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 271.30 Tm (everything else fits into it. Let me read it from the top.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 251.10 Tm (Right at the top is something called Iterable. The only thing you need to know is that 'iterable') Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 235.90 Tm (means 'you can loop over it with a for-each loop'. Below that is Collection, which is the parent of) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 220.70 Tm (most of what we use.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 200.50 Tm (Collection splits into three families. First, List - a List keeps things in order, lets you grab items by) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 185.30 Tm (their position number, and allows duplicates. Second, Set - a Set's special rule is no duplicates) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 170.10 Tm (allowed, ever. And third, Queue - which handles items at the two ends, like a line of people.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 149.90 Tm (Now look at the box sitting off to the side - Map. And here is the one thing I really want you to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 134.70 Tm (remember from this slide: Map is NOT part of the Collection family. Why? Because all the others) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 119.50 Tm (store single items - one name, one number. But a Map stores things in pairs - a key and a value,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 104.30 Tm (like a word and its dictionary meaning. Because it works in pairs, it lives in its own separate family.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 84.10 Tm (So, three families under Collection - List, Set, Queue - and Map standing on its own. Got that) Tj ET
