0.040 0.520 1.000 rg 58.00 647.00 496.00 1.40 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.420 0.420 0.460 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 631.00 Tm (ON SCREEN) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 615.00 Tm (Two code panels: a raw list with no type that fails at runtime, versus a typed list that catches the error while) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 601.50 Tm (typing. Three benefit cards.) Tj ET
0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 588.00 3.00 49.00 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 577.00 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 561.00 Tm (Before we go deeper, one quick but important idea - generics. That is the angle-bracket thing, like) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 545.80 Tm (List of String. Let me show you why it matters with the two panels.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 525.60 Tm (On the left is the old style, with no type specified. We make a list, we add the word 'Ravi', and then) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 510.40 Tm (- oops - we accidentally add the number 101. The compiler says nothing. It happily allows it. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 495.20 Tm (bug stays hidden, quietly waiting. Then later, when we pull an item out expecting a word, the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 480.00 Tm (program crashes. And it crashes at runtime - maybe in front of a customer, maybe in production.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 464.80 Tm (The worst possible time.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 444.60 Tm (On the right, we add the type - List of String, meaning 'this list holds only words'. Now when we try) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 429.40 Tm (to add the number 101, the compiler immediately stops us, right there, while we are still typing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 414.20 Tm (The mistake is caught the instant we make it.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 394.00 Tm (Think of it like a labelled jar in your kitchen. If a jar says 'Sugar' on it, you are not going to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 378.80 Tm (accidentally pour salt into it - the label protects you. Generics are that label on your collection.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 358.60 Tm (So the three benefits are: errors caught early at compile time, no need to manually convert types,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 343.40 Tm (and your code documents itself because anyone can see what the list holds. The rule is simple -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 328.20 Tm (always put the type in the angle brackets. Always.) Tj ET
