BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 621.10 Tm (It is the most natural idea in the world. A dog is an animal. A car is a vehicle. A manager is an) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 605.90 Tm (employee. In code, we say Dog extends Animal, and that means Dog automatically gets) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 590.70 Tm (everything Animal has - if Animal can eat and sleep, Dog can eat and sleep for free, without) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 575.50 Tm (rewriting it. And Dog can add its own things, like bark, and can also change, or 'override', an) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 560.30 Tm (inherited behaviour to do it its own way.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 540.10 Tm (Why is this powerful? Because of something called polymorphism - a big word for a simple idea.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 524.90 Tm (Look at the right panel - we can write Animal a equals new Dog. We are treating the dog as an) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 509.70 Tm (animal, which is fine, because a dog is an animal. And when we call eat, Java is smart enough to) Tj ET
