BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 574.60 Tm (A problem about a Logger needing to both write a file and connect to a database, then a composition) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 561.10 Tm (solution, and four benefit cards.) Tj ET
0.720 0.720 0.760 rg 58.00 547.60 3.00 49.00 re f
BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 536.60 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 520.60 Tm (Here is a piece of advice you will hear throughout your whole career as a programmer: favour) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 505.40 Tm (composition over inheritance. That sounds abstract, so let me make it concrete with the example) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 490.20 Tm (on screen.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 470.00 Tm (Suppose you want to build a Logger - something that records messages. And you want it to both) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 454.80 Tm (write to a file AND save to a database. With inheritance, you would want to extend both a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 439.60 Tm (FileWriter and a DatabaseConnector. But here is the wall you hit - Java does not allow a class to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 424.40 Tm (extend two parents. You simply cannot inherit from both. Dead end.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 404.20 Tm (Composition solves it instantly and elegantly. Instead of trying to BE a FileWriter and a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 389.00 Tm (DatabaseConnector, the Logger simply HAS one of each, as fields inside it. Then its log method) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 373.80 Tm (just asks each one to do its part. No conflict, no limit - you can compose as many helpers as you) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 358.60 Tm (want.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 338.40 Tm (The four cards list why this is better: no single-parent limit; you can swap pieces at runtime, like) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 323.20 Tm (switching the file-writer for a network-writer; your classes stay small and focused on one job; and it) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 308.00 Tm (is much easier to test, because you can slot in fake versions of the helpers.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 287.80 Tm (So the rule of thumb: inherit only when it is truly an 'is-a' relationship. When you just want to reuse) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 272.60 Tm (some behaviour, compose - put the helper inside as a field. Most of the time, composition is the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 257.40 Tm (right answer.) Tj ET
