BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 372.40 Tm (Last topic - File Input-Output, or File I-O. And this connects right back to where we started the day.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 357.20 Tm (Collections hold data in memory, which disappears when the program ends. Files solve that by) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 342.00 Tm (saving data onto the disk, where it stays. No database server needed - just a simple file. Perfect) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 326.80 Tm (for things like settings, logs, and exporting reports.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 306.60 Tm (Now, Java gives you two families of tools for files, and it is important to pick the right one. The first) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 291.40 Tm (is byte streams - these are for binary files, things that are not plain text, like images, music, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 276.20 Tm (PDFs. The second is character streams - these are for text files, and they handle the letters and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 261.00 Tm (encoding for you.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 240.80 Tm (Here is the simple rule of thumb: about ninety percent of the time you will be working with text -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 225.60 Tm (text files, CSV files, config files. So reach for character streams. They are the ones that) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 210.40 Tm (understand letters.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 190.20 Tm (And a quick but important clarification about a class called File. The File class represents a path -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 175.00 Tm (like a label or an address for a file. It can tell you things - does this file exist, how big is it - and it) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 159.80 Tm (can create or delete files. But here is the catch that surprises people: the File class does NOT read) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 144.60 Tm (or write the contents. It is just the address on the envelope, not the letter inside. To read and write) Tj ET
