BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 202.00 Tm (Three finishing touches for files. Let me take them one at a time.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 181.80 Tm (First, on the left - always close your files, safely. A file is a resource the operating system hands) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 166.60 Tm (you, and if you forget to close it, you can leak it or even lock the file so nobody else can use it. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 151.40 Tm (clean solution, just like we will see in JDBC, is try-with-resources - you declare the file in the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 136.20 Tm (brackets after try, and Java guarantees to close it for you, even if an error happens. And always) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 121.00 Tm (catch IOException, which is the error for file problems like 'file not found' or 'no permission'.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 100.80 Tm (Second, on the right - the modern, shorter way, in a package called java dot n-i-o dot file. Look) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 85.60 Tm (how short these are. Files dot writeString to write a whole file in one line. Files dot readString to) Tj ET
