BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 520.60 Tm (This slide is the grand finale - it shows everything we learned today working together in one real) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 505.40 Tm (task. Let me narrate the story of this code, in three acts.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 485.20 Tm (Act one - read. We open a CSV file with a BufferedReader, skip the first line because it is just the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 470.00 Tm (header row, then loop through every line. For each line, we split it by commas and build an) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 454.80 Tm (Employee object from the pieces, and we add each one into an ArrayList. So now our file data is) Tj ET
