BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 754.00 Tm (a queue. Comparable is the one natural order, Comparator is for flexible custom orders.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 733.80 Tm (Sets: HashSet is fastest with no order, LinkedHashSet remembers insertion order, TreeSet keeps) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 718.60 Tm (things sorted.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 698.40 Tm (Maps: HashMap is fast and unordered, TreeMap is sorted; loop with entrySet to get key and value) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 683.20 Tm (together; and for your own objects as keys, override hashCode and equals together.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 663.00 Tm (Class relationships: 'is-a' is inheritance, 'has-a' is composition or aggregation; favour composition) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 647.80 Tm (for reusing code; abstract classes are half-finished, interfaces are pure capability contracts.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 627.60 Tm (File I-O: BufferedReader and BufferedWriter for text, PrintWriter for nice formatting, the modern) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 612.40 Tm (Files class for short code, and Properties for config files.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 592.20 Tm (And the golden rules across everything: always use generics with the angle brackets; ArrayList) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 577.00 Tm (and HashMap are the right default most of the time; and always use try-with-resources when) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 561.80 Tm (working with files.) Tj ET
