BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 438.10 Tm (And that brings us to the end. Today you picked up the complete toolkit for managing data in Java) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 422.90 Tm (- holding it in memory with collections, connecting it structurally with class relationships, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 407.70 Tm (saving it to disk with file I-O.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 387.50 Tm (Here is the thought I want to leave you with. In every Spring Boot project you build from here on,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 372.30 Tm (all three of these are quietly at work, every single day. The list that holds your database results -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 357.10 Tm (that is collections. The way your entity classes relate to each other - that is class relationships. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 341.90 Tm (application dot properties file Spring reads when it starts up - that is file I-O. You did not just learn) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 326.70 Tm (three topics today; you learned the foundation under everything that comes next.) Tj ET
